	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Quaestor in Spain, named on coins of Urso, Myrtilus, and Baelo, dated by Grant to 44 and 43 under Sextus Pompey (From Imperium to Auctoritas 24f.). He also issued coins at Lilybaeum in Sicily (Ibid. 25). See Mommsen, RMW 375, note 28." .
